org.bk.ass.cluster

Class StableDBScanner<U>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bk.ass.cluster.StableDBScanner<U>

  • public class StableDBScanner<U>
extends java.lang.Object
    DBScan which processes the DB in chunks. Element clusters are generally stable: After an iteration the cluster of an element is usually the same as before. An exception is if a cluster is split into multiple clusters. In that case, only a part of the elements are retained in the previous cluster.
    Make sure to call scan(int) to actually perform clustering. Calling updateDB(PositionQueries, int) or updateDB(Collection, Function) will reset the clustering process. Make sure to always cluster all elements or to check if the clustering is done with isComplete().
    The clustering is ongoing, each call to scan(int) will continue or restart the clustering.
    When updating the DB be aware that elements are compared with == and not equals.
